definitionGroups.group: (obsolete except Britain, dialectal) Synonym of flake

entries.meaning: A small, light piece that is only loosely joined to something else, and which has a tendency to detach.
A thin piece that is chipped or peeled off from the surface of something else.
A thin piece that the flesh of some animals (such as fish) tends to break into.

verbs.description: fleak (third-person singular simple present fleaks, present participle fleaking, simple past and past participle fleaked)

entries.meaning: (transitive, obsolete, rare) Synonym of flake (“to remove (something) in fleaks or flakes (small chips or pieces)”)
